00:03:11.540 --> 00:03:15.040
What about different pharmacologic properties?

00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:23.040
Synrhodoclax and lasaftoclax have short half-lives of 4-6 hours relative to venetoclax of 26 hours.

00:03:23.040 --> 00:03:31.040
How might this impact on safety outcomes? How might this impact on TLS risk and potentially impact TLS mitigation strategies?

00:03:31.040 --> 00:03:37.040
Can we improve upon the efficacy of BCL2-based therapies in CLL and other diseases?

00:03:37.040 --> 00:03:42.040
Synrhodoclax is 14 times more pharmacologically potent than venetoclax.

00:03:42.040 --> 00:03:48.040
Does this result in improved clinical outcomes when you give it to patients?

